Installation
############

Unpacking
---------

Once the package is downloaded you can uncompress it wherever you want
but remember to **define the path to the ORBS folder into the
scripts**::

  scripts/reduction_script.py
  scripts/orbs.py

It is also recommended to create a symbolic link (under Linux or Mac)
to use the scripts from any location. Run as root::

  ln -s /link/to/orbs /usr/bin/orbs
  ln -s /link/to/orbs-optcreator /usr/bin/orbs-optcreator

Dependances
-----------

You must use Python_ 2.6 or later and install the following modules
(always try to use use the latest version):

Scipy_
~~~~~~

  |Linux| As root run::

    apt-get install python-scipy

  |Mac| Everything is explained here: http://www.scipy.org/Installing_SciPy/Mac_OS_X

Numpy_
~~~~~~

 |Linux| As root run:: 
   
    apt-get install python-numpy

 |Mac| It must already be installed
 
pyFITS_
~~~~~~~

  |Linux| As root run::
   
     apt-get install python-pyfits

  |Mac| Use Mac Ports


Parallel_ Python
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  |Linux| Download the latest version (pp-1.x.x.tar.gz), untar and once in pp-1.x.x directory run as root:: 

	    python setup.py install

  |Mac| Download the latest version (pp-1.x.x.tar.gz), untar and once in pp-1.x.x directory run as root:: 

      python setup.py build

  (For Mac only) append the following line at the beginning of the scripts ``scripts/reduction_script.py`` and ``scripts/orbs.py``::

      sys.path.append('/path/to/pp-1.x.x')




